### Structure: How Topic Clusters Work

**Three Core Elements:**

**1. Pillar Page (Central Hub)**
- Comprehensive coverage of broad topic (2,000-5,000+ words)
- Defines main subject and acts as central authority
- Links out to all related cluster content
- Serves as landing page for competitive head terms

**2. Cluster Articles (Spokes)**
- Focus on narrow subtopics related to pillar
- Each answers specific question or search intent in depth
- Target long-tail keywords
- 1,000-2,000 words typically

**3. Internal Linking Structure**
- All cluster articles link back to pillar page
- Pillar page links to all cluster articles
- Bidirectional flow of authority
- Creates semantic relationship signals for search engines

**Example Structure:**
- **Pillar**: "Complete Guide to SEO in 2025"
- **Clusters**: "Keyword Research Tools 2025," "On-Page SEO Checklist," "Link Building Strategies," "Technical SEO Fundamentals," "Local SEO Optimization"

### Why Topic Clusters Outperform Traditional SEO

**1. Topical Authority Signals**
- Demonstrates comprehensive expertise on subject
